obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (100044)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100044&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Immigration and Foreigners`
  line `Act, 2025.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st day of September, 2025, vide notification No. S.O. 3981 (E), dated 31st August, 2025, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (100045)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100045&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "accommodation" means a temporary or permanent premises of any nature, where a foreigner`
  line `is accommodated;`
  line
  line `(b) "carrier" means a person or entity, including any association of persons or company, whether`
  line `incorporated or not, who is engaged in the business of transporting passengers or cargo by air, water`
  line `or land by aircraft or ship or any other mode of transport;`
  line
  line `(c) "civil authority" means such authority as may be appointed by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf for such area as it thinks fit;`
  line
  line `(d) "entry" means entry by air, water or land;`
  line
  line `(e) "exit" means exit by air, water or land;`
  line
  line `(f) "foreigner" means a person who is not a citizen of India;`
  line
  line `(g) "immigration function" means any one of the functions relating to---`
  line
  line `(i) the visa issuance and regulation of entry into;`
  line
  line `(ii) transit through;`
  line
  line `(iii) stay in; or`
  line
  line `(iv) movement within and exit from,`
  line
  line `India, under the provisions of this Act or rules or orders or directions made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(h) "Immigration Officer" means any officer authorised by the Central Government to carry out`
  line `immigration functions or such other functions as may be prescribed and includes the Chief`
  line `Immigration Officer;`
  line
  line `(i) "immigration post" means the point of entry into and exit from India for the purpose of`
  line `immigration functions as may be notified by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(j) "keeper of accommodation" means the person in charge of the management of an`
  line `accommodation and includes any person authorised by him to perform the duties of the keeper of`
  line `the accommodation;`
  line
  line `(k) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expressions "notify"`
  line `and "notified" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(l) "order" means the instructions issued under any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(m) "other travel document" means the Emergency Certificate or Certificate of Identity or such other`
  line `travel document which has been issued by or under the authority of the Central Government or`
  line `Government of a foreign country or any other organisation as may be recognised for this purpose by`
  line `the Central Government, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(n) "passport" means a passport issued or deemed to have been issued under the provisions of the`
  line `Passport Act, 1967 (15 of 1967) and includes a passport which have been issued by or under the`
  line `authority of the Government of a foreign country subject to such conditions as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(o) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(p) "Prohibited place" means any place as the Central Government may, by order, specify in this`
  line behalf;
  line
  line `(q) "Protected area" means any area contiguous with India’s international border or any other area,`
  line `as the Central Government may, by order, specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(r) "Registration Officer" means a Registration Officer authorised by the Central Government in this`
  line `behalf for such area as it thinks fit and includes such officer authorised by him with the approval of the`
  line `Central Government to perform the duties of the Registration Officer on his behalf;`
  line
  line `(s) "Restricted area" means any area within India and outside the protected area, as the Central`
  line `Government may, by order, specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(t) "visa" means an authorisation by such authority as may be prescribed in this behalf, permitting a`
  line `foreigner to enter into or transit through or stay in or exit from the territory of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (100046)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Requirement of passport or other travel document and visa.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100046&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person proceeding from`
  line `any place outside India shall enter, or attempt to enter, India by air, water or land unless he is in`
  line `possession of a valid passport or other travel document, and in case of a foreigner, also a valid visa, and`
  line `any foreigner while present in India shall also be required to possess valid passport or other valid travel`
  line `document and valid visa, unless exempted under section 33 or through intergovernmental agreements:`
  line
  line `Provided that notwithstanding anything contained in this sub-section, no foreigner shall be allowed`
  line `to enter into or stay in India, if he is found inadmissible to do so on account of threat to national security,`
  line `sovereignty and integrity of India, relations with a foreign State or public health or on such other`
  line `grounds as the Central Government may, specify in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the decision of the Immigration Officer in this regard shall be final and binding.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 3 of the Passports Act, 1967 (15 of 1967), no`
  line `person shall depart or attempt to depart from India by air, water or land unless he is in possession of a`
  line `valid passport or other travel document and in case of a foreigner, also a valid visa:`
  line
  line `Provided that notwithstanding anything contained in this sub-section, no person shall be allowed to`
  line `depart or exit from India, if his presence is required in India by any authorised agency or on such`
  line `grounds as the Central Government may, by order, specify in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the decision of the Immigration Officer in this regard shall be final and binding.`
  line
  line `(3) The Immigration Officer may examine the passport or other travel document and visa of a`
  line `foreigner during his entry into, transit through, stay in, movement within India and also require him to`
  line `furnish such information as may be necessary and appropriate.`
  line
  line `(4) The Immigration Officer may seize a passport or other travel document of any person which has`
  line `been declared as lost or stolen or considered as damaged or forged or fraudulently obtained or on the`
  line `direction of the passport issuing authority or courts.`
  line
  line `(5) The overall supervision, direction and control on visa and related matters shall vest in and be`
  line `exercised by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (100047)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Immigration posts for entry or exit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100047&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may notify the designated`
  line `immigration posts for entry into or exit from India at such places as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(2) A designated immigration post for entry into or exit from India shall be manned by an`
  line `Immigration Officer or such other officers as may be specified by the Bureau of Immigration constituted`
  line `under section 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (100048)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Bureau of Immigration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100048&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Bureau called the Bureau of`
  line `Immigration for performing the immigration functions and such other functions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Bureau of Immigration referred to in sub-section (1) shall consist of such number of officers`
  line `appointed by the Central Government in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The general supervision, directions and control of the Bureau of Immigration, shall vest in and`
  line `be exercised by the Central Government and the overall supervision of the immigration functions and`
  line `such other functions as may be prescribed, shall vest in the officer appointed by the Central Government`
  line `as Commissioner of Bureau of Immigration.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner, Bureau of Immigration shall, in discharge of his duties under this Act, be`
  line `assisted by the Foreigners Regional Registration Officers, Foreigners Registration Officers, Chief`
  line `Immigration Officers and such Immigration Officers as may be authorised by the Central Government`
  line `in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (100049)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Registration of foreigners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100049&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The foreigners on arrival in India shall be required to register with`
  line `the Registration Officer concerned, subject to such conditions and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (100050)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to issue orders, directions or instructions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100050&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by an`
  line `order or direction or instruction, make provisions, either generally or with respect to all foreigners or`
  line `with respect to any particular foreigner or any specified class or description of foreigner, for prohibiting,`
  line `regulating or restricting the entry of foreigners into India or, their departure therefrom or their presence`
  line `or continued presence therein.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, the orders or`
  line `directions or instructions issued under this section may provide that the foreigner---`
  line
  line `(a) shall not enter India, or shall enter India only at such times and by such route and at such port`
  line `or place and subject to the observance of such conditions on arrival as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(b) shall not depart from India, or shall depart only at such times and by such route and from such`
  line `port or place and subject to the observance of such conditions on departure as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(c) shall not remain in India or in any specified area therein;`
  line
  line `(d) shall, if he has been required by order or direction or instruction under this section not to`
  line `remain in India, meet from any resources at his disposal the cost of his removal from India and of`
  line `his maintenance therein pending such removal;`
  line
  line `(e) shall remove himself to, and remain in, such area in India as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(f) shall comply with such conditions as may be specified---`
  line
  line `(i) requiring him to present himself for examination, for such information in such manner, at`
  line `such time, as may be required;`
  line
  line `(ii) requiring him to reside in a particular place;`
  line
  line `(iii) imposing any restrictions on his movements;`
  line
  line `(iv) requiring him to furnish such proof of his identity and to report such particulars to such`
  line `authority in such manner and at such time and place as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(v) requiring him to allow his photograph and biometric information, as may be specified, to`
  line `be taken and to furnish specimens of his handwriting and signature to such authority and at such`
  line `time and place as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(vi) requiring him to submit himself to such medical examination by such authority and at`
  line `such time and place as may be specified;`
  line
  line `(vii) prohibiting him from association with persons of a specified description;`
  line
  line `(viii) prohibiting him from engaging in activities of a specified description;`
  line
  line `(ix) prohibiting him from using or possessing specified articles;`
  line
  line `(x) regulating his conduct in any such particular as may be specified.`
  line
  line `(3) In addition to the foregoing, the Central Government may make provision for any matter which`
  line `is to be or may be specified and for such incidental and supplementary matters as may be expedient or`
  line `necessary for giving effect to this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Any authority specified in this behalf may, with respect to any particular foreigner, issue order`
  line `or direction or instruction under clause (f) of sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (100051)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Obligation of keeper of accommodation and others to furnish particulars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100051&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the`
  line `duty of the keeper of accommodation to submit to the Registration Officer such information in respect`
  line `of foreigners accommodated in such accommodation and in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that subject to provisions of sub-section (3), provisions of this of this sub-section shall not`
  line `be applicable to residential premises of non-commercial nature.`
  line
  line `(2) Every foreigner accommodated in such accommodation shall furnish to the keeper of`
  line `accommodation thereof such particulars as may be required by him.`
  line
  line `(3) If in any area as may be specified in this behalf, the civil authority so directs, it shall be the duty`
  line `of every person occupying or having under his control any residential premises to submit to the`
  line `Registration Officer in such manner such information in respect of foreigner accommodated in such`
  line `premises as may be specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (100052)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Obligation of Universities and Educational Institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100052&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every University and Educational`
  line `Institution or any other institution admitting any foreigner shall furnish information to the Registration`
  line `Officer in respect of such foreigner in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (100053)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Obligation of hospital, nursing home or any other medical institution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100053&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every hospital,`
  line `nursing home or any other such medical institution providing medical, lodging or sleeping facility in`
  line `their premises shall furnish information in respect of any foreigner taking indoor medical treatment or`
  line `their attendant for whom such lodging or sleeping facility has been provided to the Registration Officer`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (100054)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Visit to Protected or Restricted area or Prohibited places.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100054&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No foreigner shall enter or stay`
  line `in Protected area or Restricted area or Prohibited place without a special permit or permission granted`
  line `by such authority as may be specified by an order published in the Official Gazette in this behalf and`
  line `subject to such conditions as specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (100055)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Change of name of foreigner in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100055&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) No foreigner who was in India on the date on`
  line `which this Act came into force shall, while in India after that date, assume or use or purport to assume`
  line `or use for any purpose, any name other than that by which he was ordinarily known immediately before`
  line `the said date, except where a specific permission for change of name has been granted by such authority`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) No foreigner who has entered into India after the date on which this Act came into force shall,`
  line `while in India after the date of his entry, assume or use or purport to assume or use for any purpose, any`
  line `name other than that by which he was ordinarily known immediately before the said date of entry,`
  line `except where a specific permission for change of name has been granted by such authority as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of this section---`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "name" includes a surname; and`
  line
  line `(b) a name shall be deemed to be changed if the spelling thereof is altered.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to the assumption or use by any married woman, of`
  line `her husband's name.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (100056)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Foreigners whose movements are restricted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100056&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any foreigner in respect of whom there is`
  line `in force an order under clause (f) of sub-section (2) of section 7 requiring him to reside at a place set`
  line `apart for the residence under supervision, for a number of foreigners, shall, while residing therein, be`
  line `subject to such conditions as to maintenance, discipline and the punishment of offences and breaches`
  line `of discipline as the Central Government may from time to time by order determine.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall---`
  line
  line `(a) knowingly assist such a foreigner to escape from custody or the place set apart for his`
  line `residence, or knowingly harbour any such foreigner; or`
  line
  line `(b) give such a foreigner any assistance with intent thereby to prevent, hinder or interfere with`
  line `the apprehension of such a foreigner.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by order, provide for regulating access to, and the conduct of`
  line `persons in, places in India where such a foreigner whose movements are restricted is lodged, and for`
  line `prohibiting or regulating the dispatch or conveyance from outside such places to or for such a foreigner`
  line `therein of such articles as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (100057)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to control places frequented by foreigners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100057&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The civil authority may, subject to`
  line `such conditions as may be prescribed, direct the owner or keeper having control of any premises`
  line `frequented by any foreigner---`
  line
  line `(a) to close such premises either entirely or during specified periods;`
  line
  line `(b) to use or permit the use of such premises only under such conditions as may be`
  line `specified; or`
  line
  line `(c) to refuse admission to such premises either to all foreigners or to any specified foreigner`
  line `or class of foreigners.`
  line
  line `(2) A person to whom any direction has been given under sub-section (1) shall not, while such`
  line `direction remains in force, use or permit to be used any other premises for any of the aforesaid purposes,`
  line `except with the previous permission in writing of the civil authority and in accordance with any`
  line `conditions which that authority may think fit to impose.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person to whom any direction has been given under sub-section (1) and who is aggrieved`
  line `thereby may, within thirty days from the date of such direction, appeal to the Central Government, and`
  line `the decision of the Central Government in the matter shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (100058)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Foreigner who is national of more than one foreign country.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100058&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `When a foreigner, while in`
  line `India with a valid passport or other travel document and valid visa, is recognised as a national by the`
  line `law of more than one foreign country, the civil authority or Immigration Officer may, after due`
  line `verification of all available documents and inquiry, treat that foreigner as the national of the country on`
  line `whose passport or travel document he had entered into India or with which he appears to be most closely`
  line `connected for the time being and the decision of civil authority or Immigration Officer in this regard`
  line `shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government, either of its own motion or on an application by the foreigner`
  line `concerned, may revise any such decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (100059)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Burden of proof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100059&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `If in any case, not falling under section15, any question arise with reference`
  line `to this Act or any rule or order made or direction given thereunder, whether any person is or is not a`
  line `foreigner of a particular class or description, the onus of proving that such person is not a foreigner or`
  line `is not a foreigner of such particular class or description, as the case may be, shall, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Bharatiya Sakshya Adhiniyam, 2023 (47 of 2023), lie upon such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (100060)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Obligation of carriers and like.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100060&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The carrier landing or embarking at a port or place in`
  line `India shall furnish to a civil authority or Immigration Officer---`
  line
  line `(i) the passenger and crew manifest;`
  line
  line `(ii) the advance passenger information data of passengers and crew on board of such aircraft,`
  line `vessel or other mode of transport, as the case may be; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the passenger name record information of passengers arriving or departing,`
  line
  line `in such form, containing such particulars, in such manner and within such time, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the expression "passenger name record information" means`
  line `the records prepared by an operator of any aircraft or vessel or other mode of transport or his authorised`
  line `agent for each journey booked by or on behalf of any passenger.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the information referred to in sub-section (1) is not furnished to civil authority or`
  line `Immigration Officer within the prescribed time and manner or false information is furnished and if civil`
  line `authority or Immigration Officer is satisfied that there was no sufficient cause for such delay in`
  line `furnishing the information or in the manner prescribed, the carrier shall be liable to such penalty`
  line `specified in section 18 for each such information:`
  line
  line `Provided that no penalty shall be imposed without giving the carrier an opportunity of being heard`
  line `in the matter.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by the penalty imposed under sub-section (3), may prefer an appeal to`
  line `such authority in such form, manner and accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) Every such appeal shall be preferred within a period of thirty days from the date of the order`
  line `appealed against:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate authority may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from preferring the appeal within the said period of thirty days, permit the appellant to`
  line `prefer the appeal within a further period not exceeding thirty days.`
  line
  line `(6) On receipt of any such appeal, the appellate authority shall, after giving the parties an opportunity`
  line `of being heard and after making such inquiry as it deems proper, make such order, as it may think fit,`
  line `confirming, modifying or reversing the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(7) Any District Magistrate or any Commissioner of Police or, where there is no Commissioner of`
  line `Police, any Superintendent of Police or the civil authority or Immigration Officer may, for any purpose`
  line `connected with the enforcement of this Act or any rule or any order made thereunder, require the carrier`
  line `to furnish such information as may be prescribed in respect of passengers or members of the crew on`
  line `such aircraft, vessel or other mode of transport, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(8) Any passenger on such carrier and any member of the crew of such carrier shall furnish to the`
  line `carrier, any information required by him for the purpose of furnishing the information referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) or for furnishing the information required under sub-section (7).`
  line
  line `(9) If any foreigner whose entry has been refused, such foreigner shall be handed over to the carrier`
  line `by the Immigration Officer and it shall be the responsibility of that carrier to ensure his removal from`
  line `India without delay.`
  line
  line `(10) If any foreigner enters into India in contravention of any provisions of this Act or any rule or`
  line `order made thereunder, the civil authority or Immigration Officer may, within two months from the date`
  line `of such entry, direct the carrier on which such entry was effected to provide accommodation, otherwise`
  line `than at the expense of Central Government, on such aircraft or a vessel or any other mode of transport`
  line `for the purpose of removing the said foreigner from India.`
  line
  line `(11) The carrier which is about to carry passengers from a port or place in India to any destination`
  line `outside India, if so directed by the Central Government and on tender of payment therefor at the current`
  line `rates, shall provide on the aircraft or vessel or any other mode of transport, accommodation to such port`
  line `or place outside India, being a port or place at which the aircraft or vessel or any other mode of transport`
  line `is due to call, as the Central Government may specify, for any foreigner ordered under section 7 not to`
  line `remain in India and for his dependents, if any, travelling with him.`
  line
  line `(12) The carrier shall not cause or permit the aircraft or vessel or any other mode of transport to`
  line `depart from a port or place in India until a clearance has been obtained from the Immigration Officer`
  line `on submission of general declaration in such form, manner and with such particulars, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(13) For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(a) "carrier" shall also include pilot of aircraft, master of vessel, or company representative or`
  line `station manager or operator of such aircraft or vessel or any other mode of transport or any person`
  line `authorised by such carrier to discharge on his behalf any of the duties imposed on him by this section;`
  line
  line `(b) "passenger" means any person not being a bona fide member of the crew, travelling or seeking`
  line `to travel on an aircraft or a vessel or any other mode of transport.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (100061)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Liability of carrier to pay penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100061&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The carrier, for contravention of the provisions of`
  line `section 17, shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to fifty thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (100062)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Liability of carriers for passengers brought into India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100062&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the civil authority or`
  line `Immigration Officer is of the opinion that any carrier has brought a person, in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of section 3 and rules or orders made thereunder, into India, he may, by order impose a`
  line `penalty which shall not be less than two lakh rupees, but may extend to five lakh rupees, on such carrier:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be passed without giving the carrier an opportunity of being heard in`
  line `the matter.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by an order made under sub-section (1), may prefer an appeal to such`
  line `authority in such form, manner and accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every such appeal shall be preferred within a period of thirty days from the date of the order`
  line `appealed against:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate authority may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from preferring the appeal within the said period of thirty days, permit the appellant to`
  line `prefer the appeal within a further period of thirty days.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of any such appeal, the appellate authority shall, after giving the parties a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard and after making such inquiry as it deems proper, make such order, as it`
  line `may think fit, confirming, modifying or reversing the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any penalty imposed under this section is not paid, the civil authority or Immigration`
  line `Officer may recover the penalty so payable by---`
  line
  line `(a) seizing or detaining the aircraft or the ship or any other mode of transport of the carrier;`
  line
  line `(b) seizing, detaining or selling any goods or properties belonging to the carrier; or`
  line
  line `(c) such other means as may be notified.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (100063)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Contravention or attempts to contravene provisions of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100063&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who`
  line `contravenes or attempts to contravene, or abets or attempts to abet, or does any act preparatory to a`
  line `contravention of, any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule or order made or direction given`
  line `thereunder, or fails to comply with any direction given in pursuance of any such order, shall be deemed`
  line `to have contravened the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who, knowing or having reasonable cause to believe that any other person has`
  line `contravened the provisions of this Act or of any rule or order made or direction given thereunder, gives`
  line `that other person any assistance with intent thereby to prevent, hinder or otherwise interfere with his`
  line `arrest, trial or punishment for the said contravention shall be deemed to have a betted that contravention.`
  line
  line `(3) The carrier, by means of which any foreigner enters or leaves India in contravention of this Act`
  line `or any rule or order made thereunder, or direction given in pursuance of section 7 shall, unless he proves`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the said contravention, be deemed to have contravened`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (100064)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Penalty for entry without valid passport or other travel document.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100064&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Any foreigner who`
  line `enters into any area in India without a valid passport or other travel document, including visa required`
  line `for such entry in contravention of provisions of section 3 of this Act or of any rule or order made`
  line `thereunder or any direction given in pursuance thereof, shall be punishable with an imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to five years or with fine which may extend to five lakh rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (100151)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Penalty for using or supplying forged or fraudulently obtained passport or other travel document and visa.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100151&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Whoever knowingly uses or supplies a forged or fraudulently obtained passport`
  line `or other travel document or visa for entering into India or staying in or exiting from India, shall be`
  line `punishable with an imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than two years, but may extend to`
  line `seven years and shall also be liable to fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend`
  line `to ten lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that any attempt for above mentioned use of forged or fraudulently obtained passport or`
  line `any other travel document or visa found for such entry or exit from India shall also be treated as an`
  line `offence under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (100066)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Penalty for contraventions of other provisions of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100066&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line Whoever,---
  line
  line `(a) being a foreigner, remains in any area in India for a period exceeding the period for which the`
  line `visa was issued to him or stays in India without a valid passport or other valid travel document in`
  line `contravention of provisions of section 3 or does any act in violation of the conditions of the valid`
  line `visa issued to him for his entry and stay in India or any part thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) contravenes any other provisions of this Act, other than sections 17 and 19, or of any rule or`
  line `order made thereunder or any direction or instruction given in pursuance of this Act or such order`
  line `or direction or instruction for which, no specific punishment is provided under this Act,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with an imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or with a fine`
  line `which may extend to three lakh rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (100067)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Penalty for abetment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100067&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever abets any offence punishable under sections 21 or 22 or`
  line `23 shall, if the act abetted is committed in consequence of the abetment, be punishable with the same`
  line `punishment as provided for those offences.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(i) an act or offence is said to be committed in consequence of the abetment, when it is committed`
  line `in consequence of the instigation, or in pursuance of the conspiracy, or with the aid which constitutes`
  line `the offence;`
  line
  line `(ii) the expression "abetment" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it under section 45 of`
  line `the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (100068)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Compounding of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100068&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Bharatiya`
  line `Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023 (46 of 2023), any offence punishable under sections 21, 23 or section`
  line `24 whether committed by an individual or a company or an organisation or any officer or employee or`
  line `a representative thereof, may, either before the institution of prosecution or during trial, be compounded`
  line `by such officers or authorities and for such sums as the Central Government may, by notification,`
  line `specify in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that the sum so specified shall not, in any case, exceed the maximum amount of the fine`
  line `which may be imposed under sections 21 or 23 for the offence so compounded.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply to an offence committed, by an individual or a`
  line `company or an organisation or any officer or employee or representative thereof within a period of three`
  line `years from the date on which a similar offence committed by it or him was compounded under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(3) Every officer or authority referred to in sub-section (1) shall exercise the powers to compound`
  line `an offence, subject to the directions, control and supervision of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any offence is compounded before the institution of any prosecution or before`
  line `commencement of trial, no prosecution shall be instituted in relation to such offence, against the`
  line `offender in relation to whom the offence is so compounded.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the compounding of an offence is made after the institution of prosecution or during trial,`
  line `such compounding shall be brought by the authority specified for such compounding in writing, to the`
  line `notice of the court in which the prosecution or trial is pending and on such notice of the compounding`
  line `of offences being given, the individual or the company or the organisation or any officer or employee`
  line `in relation to whom the offence is so compounded shall be discharged.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purposes of this section, any second or subsequent offence committed after the expiry of`
  line `a period of three years from the date on which the offence was previously compounded, shall be deemed`
  line `to be a first offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (100069)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100069&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Any officer of police, not below the rank of a Head Constable may arrest`
  line `without warrant any person who has contravened or against whom a reasonable suspicion exists that he`
  line `has contravened section 3 or any rule or order made thereof and the provisions of section 58 of the`
  line `Bharatiya Nagarik Suraksha Sanhita, 2023 (46 of 2023) shall, so far as may be, apply in the case of any`
  line `such arrest.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (100070)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to give effect to orders, directions, and like.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100070&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any authority empowered by or`
  line `under or in pursuance of the provisions of this Act or rule or order made thereunder to give any direction`
  line `or to exercise any other power may, in addition to any other action expressly provided for in this Act,`
  line `take or cause to be taken such steps and use, or cause to be used, such force as may, in its opinion, be`
  line `reasonably necessary for securing compliance with such direction or for preventing or rectifying any`
  line `breach thereof, or for the effective exercise of such power, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Any police officer, not below the rank of Head Constable, may take such steps and use such`
  line `force as may, in his opinion, be reasonably necessary for securing compliance with any rule or order`
  line `made or direction given under or in pursuance of the provisions of this Act or for preventing or`
  line `rectifying any breach of such rule or order or direction.`
  line
  line `(3) The power conferred by this section shall be deemed to confer upon any person acting in exercise`
  line `thereof a right of access to any land or other property whatsoever.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (100071)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to delegate authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100071&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification, direct that any`
  line `power or functions which may be exercised or performed by it under this Act or by any rule or order`
  line `made thereunder, subject to such conditions, if any, as it may specify in such notification, be exercised`
  line `or performed---`
  line
  line `(a) by such officer or authority subordinate to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) by any State Government or by any officer or authority subordinate to such Government or`
  line `any officer or authority authorised by such Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (100072)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power of removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100072&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by general or special order, direct the`
  line `removal of a foreigner from India for contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or any rule or`
  line `order made thereunder or an adverse security report, and thereupon any officer of the Government shall`
  line `have all reasonable powers necessary to enforce such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (100073)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100073&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) such other functions to be carried out by Immigration Officer under clause (h) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions subject to which the other travel document issued under clause (m) of`
  line `section 2;`
  line
  line `(c) the conditions subject to which the passport issued under clause (n) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(d) the authority authorised to grant visa under clause (t) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(e) such other functions to be performed by the Bureau of Immigration under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of appointment of officers of the Bureau of Immigration under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(g) the other functions which shall vest in the officers appointed by the Central Government as`
  line `Commissioners of the Bureau of Immigration under sub-section (3) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(h) the conditions and the manner subject to which the foreigners on arrival in India shall be`
  line `required to register with the Registration Officer under section 6;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of submission of the information of foreigners to the Registration Officer by the`
  line `keeper of accommodation under section 8;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of submission of the information of foreigners to the Registration Officer by the`
  line `Universities and Educational Institutions under section 9;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of submission of the information of foreigners to the Registration Officer by the`
  line `hospitals, nursing homes and other medical institutions under section 10;`
  line
  line `(l) the authority and the manner for change of name of a foreigner subject to a specific permission`
  line `under sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(m) the restriction of the dispatch of such articles to or for a foreigner under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 13;`
  line
  line `(n) the conditions subject to which the civil authority may exercise the power to control places`
  line `frequented by foreigners under section 14;`
  line
  line `(o) the form, particulars, the manner and the time within which the information to be furnished`
  line `by carrier to the civil authority or Immigration Officer under sub-section (1) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(p) the appellate authority, form, manner and the fee to be accompanied for filing an appeal under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(q) the information to be required by District Magistrate or any Commissioner of Police from the`
  line `carrier under sub-section (7) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(r) the form, manner and such particulars to be submitted by the carrier to the Immigration Officer`
  line `under sub-section (12) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(s) the appellate authority, form, manner and the fee to be accompanied for filing an appeal under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(t) any matter which is to be or may be prescribed or in respect of which provision is to be made`
  line `by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (100074)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Rules to be laid Before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100074&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (100075)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100075&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `No suit or any other proceeding shall lie against any`
  line `person for anything done, or intended to be done in good faith under this Act or any rule or order made`
  line thereunder.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (100076)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power to exempt in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100076&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by order published in`
  line `the Official Gazette, declare that all or any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule or order made`
  line `thereunder shall not apply, or shall apply only in such circumstances or with such exceptions or`
  line `modifications or subject to such conditions as may be specified in such order, to or in relation to---`
  line
  line `(a) the citizens or class of citizens of any such country as may be so specified; or`
  line
  line `(b) any other individual foreigner or class or description of foreigner.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, if it is of the opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to do in`
  line `the public interest or to fulfil the international obligation, by order published in the Official Gazette and`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be specified therein, exempt any carrier or class of carriers from the`
  line `operations of all or any of the provisions of this Act and may, as often as may be necessary, revoke or`
  line `modify such order.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (100077)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100077&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (100078)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100078&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of three`
  line `years from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (100079)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406&sectionId=100079&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00022_2025-13_1757572252406
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Passport (Entry into India) Act, 1920 (34 of 1920), the`
  line `Registration of Foreigners Act, 1939 (16 of 1939), the Foreigners Act, 1946 (31 of 1946) and the`
  line `Immigration (Carriers’ Liability) Act, 2000 (52 of 2000) (hereinafter referred to as repealed Acts) are`
  line `hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken or purported to have been done`
  line `or taken, including any rules, orders, directions, instructions, regulations or any proceedings made or`
  line `issued or taken or given or any penalty or fine imposed under the repealed Acts shall, in so far as it is`
  line `not inconsistent with the provision of this Act, be deemed to have been done or taken under the`
  line `corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The mention of the particular matters referred to in sub-section (2) shall not be held to prejudice`
  line `or affect the general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with regard`
  line `to the effect of repeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
